16147

16148<h2>

16149Choose the Perfect Vessel Faucet for Your Bathroom Sink</h2>

16150

16151

16152<p>

16153If you&rsquo;re looking for a beautiful new statement piece for your bathroom, it&rsquo;s hard to go wrong with a vessel bathroom sink. Known for a basin that extends above or sits completely atop the counter, vessel sinks act as a luxurious focal point for traditional and modern style bathrooms alike.</p>

16154

16155

16156<p>

16157&nbsp;</p>

16158

16159

16160<p>

16161That all being said, a vessel sink is nothing without its faucet. As with any new sink, it&rsquo;s absolutely essential to pick a faucet with the right height, style, and installation type&mdash;but this process can be especially tricky for vessel vanity faucets because of the unique vessel sink setup.</p>

16162

16163

16164<p>

16165&nbsp;</p>

16166

16167

16168<p>

16169To make the process a bit easier, we&rsquo;ve outlined everything you need to know about vessel sink faucets&mdash;from how to choose the right size, to the different designs and finishes, to how to install this type of faucet in your new bathroom.</p>

16170

16171

16172<p>

16173&nbsp;</p>

16174

16175

16176<h2>

16177What is a Vessel Sink Faucet?</h2>

16178

16179

16180<p>

16181Because of their unique above-vanity configuration, vessel bathroom sinks require special vessel vanity faucets. Technically, vessel sinks can use any kind of faucet&mdash;what matters is the height of the faucet. Because a vessel sink sits on top of the vanity countertop, the faucet has to be tall enough to fit the sink correctly, which often means these faucets are typically single hole faucets or wall-mounted faucets.</p>

16182

16183

16184<p>

16185&nbsp;</p>

16186

16187

16188<h2>

16189How to Choose the Right Size Vessel Faucet</h2>

16190

16191

16192<p>

16193Because each vessel sink is different, it will take a little bit of work to find a vessel faucet that fits perfectly. The most important factor you will need to consider is height, followed by the spout reach. Before purchasing a vessel faucet, you&rsquo;ll also need to determine the size of vanity and which sink you will be installing.</p>

16194

16195

16196<p>

16197&nbsp;</p>

16198

16199

16200<h3>

162011. Consider the Vanity Cabinet Height</h3>

16202

16203

16204<p>

16205Before you purchase the vessel faucet&mdash;or vessel sink, for that matter&mdash;consider the size and height of your vanity cabinets. Vanities with vessel sinks often need to be lower than a standard vanity because of the added height of the vessel sink. If you have a standard vanity, keeping it at a common height for other common sinks, the faucet and the sink may be too high.</p>

16206

16207

16208<p>

16209&nbsp;</p>

16210

16211

16212<p>

16213For the height of your vanity, you will need to consider the people this sink will be accommodating. If you will have small children around, ensure the vanity is low enough that they will be able to wash their hands despite the added height of the vessel sink. Don&rsquo;t forget, they need to be tall enough to reach the vessel faucet as well!</p>

16214

16215

16216<p>

16217&nbsp;</p>

16218

16219

16220<h3>

162212. Measure Your Vessel Sink</h3>

16222

16223

16224<p>

16225One of the most important measurements you&rsquo;ll take is that of the vessel sink itself. Measure how high the sink rises above the countertop to ensure you get a faucet that&rsquo;s tall enough to reach the sink. Keep in mind that a top-mounted sink can add six inches and sometimes more to the overall vanity height.</p>

16226

16227

16228<p>

16229&nbsp;</p>

16230

16231

16232<p>

16233Additionally, consider how much counter space the sink will take up. If the sink leaves no room behind it to install the faucet, you may need to opt for a wall-mount vessel faucet or install your faucet to the side&mdash;in which case, you may be limited to single-hole faucets.</p>

16234

16235

16236<p>

16237&nbsp;</p>

16238

16239

16240<h3>

162413. Calculate the Ideal Vessel Faucet Height</h3>

16242

16243

16244<p>

16245With your vessel sink measurements in hand, you&rsquo;re able to determine the correct height vessel vanity faucet. As a general rule of thumb, the vessel faucet should be installed high enough that there is a distance of at least six inches from the bottom of the spout to the bottom of the sink. Six inches is a large enough distance that it gives you enough space to comfortably wash your hands, without splashing. If you go more than six inches, you risk more splashing in the vessel sink. Vessel faucets are generally 12&rdquo; to 17&rdquo; in height.</p>

16246

16247

16248<p>

16249&nbsp;</p>

16250

16251

16252<h3>

162534. Pick the Location of the Faucet</h3>

16254

16255

16256<p>

16257When looking at all your vessel faucet options, you&rsquo;ll want to think about the location of this faucet. You have two options&mdash;directly behind the sink installed in the wall or on the countertop, or to the side, installed in the countertop. This will be determined based on personal preference or the sink you choose.</p>

16258

16259

16260<p>

16261&nbsp;</p>

16262

16263

16264<p>

16265Some sinks come with a faucet hole integrated into it, which means you may or may not be able to select a different faucet than the one that came with the sink. If the faucet hole in the sink is proprietary to the faucet that comes with the sink, you will need to use that faucet. Take this into consideration when searching for the right sink, because some sinks offer you the option to choose which faucet to install with the sink.</p>

16266

16267

16268<p>

16269&nbsp;</p>

16270

16271

16272<h2>

16273Different Types of Vessel Faucets</h2>

16274

16275

16276<p>

16277The most common type of vessel faucets are single-hole and wall-mounted faucets, which are more likely to accommodate the height you need. That being said, vessel vanity styles are far from limiting. Whether your bathroom style is modern, contemporary, minimalist, farmhouse, or another style Vevano Home has a vessel sink faucet for you.</p>

16278

16279

16280<p>

16281&nbsp;</p>

16282

16283

16284<p>

16285If you are going for a modern, sleek look, consider purchasing a tall, <a href="https://vevano.com/product/45782-k-73159-7-tt-composed-tall-vessel-pure-single-handle-bathroom-faucet-in-vibrant-titanium/">

16286single handle faucet in titanium</a>

16287. If you are wanting to achieve a minimalist look, then a <a href="https://vevano.com/product/45765-k-14404-4a-bl-purist-tall-vessel-single-handle-bathroom-faucet-in-matte-black/">

16288matte black vessel sink faucet</a>

16289 is good option. For a contemporary look, consider a <a href="https://vevano.com/product/36332-l-az111bn-valle-vessel-bathroom-faucet-in-brushed-nickel-787-spout-height/">

16290single handle faucet in brushed nickel</a>

16291. If your bathroom is traditional and classic, a <a href="https://vevano.com/product/44265-797lf-cassidy-vessel-vanity-faucet-in-chrome/">

16292chrome finish faucet with elegant details</a>

16293 is the perfect choice for you.</p>

16294

16295

16296<p>

16297&nbsp;</p>

16298

16299

16300<h2>

16301How to Install a Vessel Sink Faucet</h2>

16302

16303

16304<p>

16305When installing a vessel sink faucet, you can do it yourself with precise measurements, or you can hire a plumber to do it for you. There are three different types of installation of vessel faucets; you choose based on where you&rsquo;d like your faucet placed.</p>

16306

16307

16308<p>

16309&nbsp;</p>

16310

16311

16312<p>

16313A wall-mount faucet places the faucet on the wall directly behind the sink. A deck-mount faucet is installed on the countertop, either behind or just to the side of the sink. A sink-mount faucet is the easiest to install because the faucet is on the sink itself.</p>

16314

16315

16316<p>

16317&nbsp;</p>

16318

16319

16320<p>

16321We&rsquo;ll walk you through a step-by-step can so you can confidently install your new bathroom vessel sink faucet.</p>

16322

16323

16324<p>

16325&nbsp;</p>

16326

16327

16328<h3>

16329Wall-mounted Faucet</h3>

16330

16331

16332<p>

16333<em>

16334*This is the most difficult type of faucet to install, so consider hiring a plumber to do it for you.</em>

16335</p>

16336

16337

16338<ol>

16339

16340 <li>

16341<strong>

16342Check the plumbing:</strong>

16343 Hire a plumber to handle the water supply and connections.</li>

16344

16345 <li>

16346<strong>

16347Determine the faucet height:</strong>

16348 Use a pencil and ruler to measure and make sure there is a 1&rdquo; gap between the bottom of the faucet and the top of the sink.</li>

16349

16350 <li>

16351<strong>

16352Drill holes in the wall:</strong>

16353 Drill holes where you marked with your pencil where the faucet will be going. Verify that there are no pipes or anything else in the wall where you will be drilling.</li>

16354

16355 <li>

16356<strong>

16357Attach the spout:</strong>

16358 Use the hardware provided by the faucet manufacturer to attach the spout to the wall and position it in the correct place.</li>

16359

16360 <li>

16361<strong>

16362Attach necessary hardware:</strong>

16363 Now is the time to attach the faucet handles and hot and cold taps. Make sure everything is securely put in its place.</li>

16364

16365</ol>

16366

16367

16368<p>

16369&nbsp;</p>

16370

16371

16372<h3>

16373Deck-mounted Faucet &amp; Sink-mounted Faucet</h3>

16374

16375

16376<p>

16377Deck-mounted is the most common type of faucet and you only need to know the height of the sink. Sink-mounted faucets are overall the easiest type of faucet to install and little skill is required. Because these installations are more simple, you can follow the instructions provided by the faucet manufacturer.</p>

16378

16379

16380<p>

16381&nbsp;</p>

16382

16383

16384<h2>

16385Vessel Faucet FAQs</h2>

16386

16387

16388<h3>

16389<em>

16390Can you use a vessel faucet with a regular sink?</em>

16391</h3>

16392

16393

16394<p>

16395Your existing plumbing connections can work with just about any vessel sink. If you are unsure if your specific sink can work with a vessel faucet, call a plumber and ask them to come take a look at your plumbing connections and the sink you have. However, keep in mind that vessel faucets are typically 12&rdquo; to 17&rdquo; tall, so the depth of your sink will determine how well a vessel faucet would work.</p>

16396

16397

16398<p>

16399&nbsp;</p>

16400

16401

16402<h3>

16403<em>

16404How far away should the vessel faucet be from the sink?</em>

16405</h3>

16406

16407

16408<p>

16409The spout of the vessel faucet should be at least six inches from the drain in the vessel sink. The distance from the faucet to the sink will depend on vanity space and the type of faucet you select.</p>

16410

16411

16412<p>

16413&nbsp;</p>

16414

16415

16416<h3>

16417<em>

16418How tall should the vessel faucet be?</em>

16419</h3>

16420

16421

16422<p>

16423A vessel faucet typically has a height of 12&ndash;17&rdquo;. You can select the height of your faucet based on the style you&rsquo;d like, the space you have available, and the size of your vessel sink.</p>

16424

16425

16426<p>

16427&nbsp;</p>

16428

16437 are happy to help you put together your dream bathroom. Happy designing!</p>

16655{"props":{"pageProps":{"error":"","query":{"slug":"faucets-vanity-vessel"},"template":null,"category":{"title":"Vessel Bathroom Faucets","treeIndex":3,"slug":"faucets-vanity-vessel","heroBanner":"","_id":"5d7a6dcbdf6b5d0017c1e92b","heroText":{"css":"","html":"\u003cdiv style=\"width:80%; margin:auto; margin-top: 120px; margin-bottom: 120px;\"\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003eChoose the Perfect Vessel Faucet for Your Bathroom Sink\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026rsquo;re looking for a beautiful new statement piece for your bathroom, it\u0026rsquo;s hard to go wrong with a vessel bathroom sink. Known for a basin that extends above or sits completely atop the counter, vessel sinks act as a luxurious focal point for traditional and modern style bathrooms alike.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThat all being said, a vessel sink is nothing without its faucet. As with any new sink, it\u0026rsquo;s absolutely essential to pick a faucet with the right height, style, and installation type\u0026mdash;but this process can be especially tricky for vessel vanity faucets because of the unique vessel sink setup.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo make the process a bit easier, we\u0026rsquo;ve outlined everything you need to know about vessel sink faucets\u0026mdash;from how to choose the right size, to the different designs and finishes, to how to install this type of faucet in your new bathroom.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eWhat is a Vessel Sink Faucet?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBecause of their unique above-vanity configuration, vessel bathroom sinks require special vessel vanity faucets. Technically, vessel sinks can use any kind of faucet\u0026mdash;what matters is the height of the faucet. Because a vessel sink sits on top of the vanity countertop, the faucet has to be tall enough to fit the sink correctly, which often means these faucets are typically single hole faucets or wall-mounted faucets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eHow to Choose the Right Size Vessel Faucet\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBecause each vessel sink is different, it will take a little bit of work to find a vessel faucet that fits perfectly. The most important factor you will need to consider is height, followed by the spout reach. Before purchasing a vessel faucet, you\u0026rsquo;ll also need to determine the size of vanity and which sink you will be installing.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e1. Consider the Vanity Cabinet Height\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eBefore you purchase the vessel faucet\u0026mdash;or vessel sink, for that matter\u0026mdash;consider the size and height of your vanity cabinets. Vanities with vessel sinks often need to be lower than a standard vanity because of the added height of the vessel sink. If you have a standard vanity, keeping it at a common height for other common sinks, the faucet and the sink may be too high.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor the height of your vanity, you will need to consider the people this sink will be accommodating. If you will have small children around, ensure the vanity is low enough that they will be able to wash their hands despite the added height of the vessel sink. Don\u0026rsquo;t forget, they need to be tall enough to reach the vessel faucet as well!\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e2. Measure Your Vessel Sink\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOne of the most important measurements you\u0026rsquo;ll take is that of the vessel sink itself. Measure how high the sink rises above the countertop to ensure you get a faucet that\u0026rsquo;s tall enough to reach the sink. Keep in mind that a top-mounted sink can add six inches and sometimes more to the overall vanity height.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAdditionally, consider how much counter space the sink will take up. If the sink leaves no room behind it to install the faucet, you may need to opt for a wall-mount vessel faucet or install your faucet to the side\u0026mdash;in which case, you may be limited to single-hole faucets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e3. Calculate the Ideal Vessel Faucet Height\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith your vessel sink measurements in hand, you\u0026rsquo;re able to determine the correct height vessel vanity faucet. As a general rule of thumb, the vessel faucet should be installed high enough that there is a distance of at least six inches from the bottom of the spout to the bottom of the sink. Six inches is a large enough distance that it gives you enough space to comfortably wash your hands, without splashing. If you go more than six inches, you risk more splashing in the vessel sink. Vessel faucets are generally 12\u0026rdquo; to 17\u0026rdquo; in height.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e4. Pick the Location of the Faucet\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen looking at all your vessel faucet options, you\u0026rsquo;ll want to think about the location of this faucet. You have two options\u0026mdash;directly behind the sink installed in the wall or on the countertop, or to the side, installed in the countertop. This will be determined based on personal preference or the sink you choose.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSome sinks come with a faucet hole integrated into it, which means you may or may not be able to select a different faucet than the one that came with the sink. If the faucet hole in the sink is proprietary to the faucet that comes with the sink, you will need to use that faucet. Take this into consideration when searching for the right sink, because some sinks offer you the option to choose which faucet to install with the sink.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eDifferent Types of Vessel Faucets\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe most common type of vessel faucets are single-hole and wall-mounted faucets, which are more likely to accommodate the height you need. That being said, vessel vanity styles are far from limiting. There are three different types of installation of vessel faucets; you choose based on where you\u0026rsquo;d like your faucet placed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA wall-mount faucet places the faucet on the wall directly behind the sink. A deck-mount faucet is installed on the countertop, either behind or just to the side of the sink. A sink-mount faucet is the easiest to install because the faucet is on the sink itself.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe\u0026rsquo;ll walk you through a step-by-step can so you can confidently install your new bathroom vessel sink faucet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWall-mounted Faucet\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003e*This is the most difficult type of faucet to install, so consider hiring a plumber to do it for you.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCheck the plumbing:\u003c/strong\u003e Hire a plumber to handle the water supply and connections.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDetermine the faucet height:\u003c/strong\u003e Use a pencil and ruler to measure and make sure there is a 1\u0026rdquo; gap between the bottom of the faucet and the top of the sink.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDrill holes in the wall:\u003c/strong\u003e Drill holes where you marked with your pencil where the faucet will be going. Verify that there are no pipes or anything else in the wall where you will be drilling.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttach the spout:\u003c/strong\u003e Use the hardware provided by the faucet manufacturer to attach the spout to the wall and position it in the correct place.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAttach necessary hardware:\u003c/strong\u003e Now is the time to attach the faucet handles and hot and cold taps. Make sure everything is securely put in its place.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eDeck-mounted Faucet \u0026amp; Sink-mounted Faucet\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDeck-mounted is the most common type of faucet and you only need to know the height of the sink. Sink-mounted faucets are overall the easiest type of faucet to install and little skill is required. Because these installations are more simple, you can follow the instructions provided by the faucet manufacturer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eVessel Faucet FAQs\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cem\u003eCan you use a vessel faucet with a regular sink?\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYour existing plumbing connections can work with just about any vessel sink. The high-tech capacitance sensing capabilities of Touch2O.xt faucets allow the flow of water to be activated by breaking the capacitance field anywhere around the device, unlike traditional hands-free infrared sensors which require your hands be in a particular place and are sensitive to lighting conditions and clothing and skin color.
